### CRIT-7 🆕: Search Input Passes Unsanitized to `.ilike()` — SQL Wildcard Injection

**Location:** [CarianPage.tsx L35-46](file:///c:/Users/Cyborg%2015/Desktop/JPP-POLISAS-main/src/pages/CarianPage.tsx#L35-L46)

```typescript
// Line 35-38
const { data: acts } = await supabase
  .from('club_activities')
  .select('*')
  .ilike('title', `%${query}%`)  // ← User input directly interpolated
  .limit(10);
```

**Problem:** The `query` value comes directly from `searchParams.get('q')`. While Supabase's PostgREST parameterizes the SQL (preventing classic SQL injection), the `%` and `_` wildcards in `ILIKE` are **not escaped**. A user searching for `%` will match ALL rows, and `___` matches any 3-character title. This enables **data enumeration** of titles across all clubs without RLS filtering.

Additionally, `select('*')` fetches ALL columns from `club_activities` and `club_reports` — including `user_id`, `budget`, etc. — for ANY club, with **no club_id scoping**. This is a **cross-club data leak**.

```diff
+// Escape SQL wildcards
+const escapedQuery = query.replace(/[%_]/g, '\\$&');
 const { data: acts } = await supabase
   .from('club_activities')
-  .select('*')
-  .ilike('title', `%${query}%`)
+  .select('id, title, status, club_id')
+  .ilike('title', `%${escapedQuery}%`)
   .limit(10);
```

> [!CAUTION]
> The search page returns `select('*')` from `club_activities` and `club_reports` with NO club scoping. Any user can search and see data from all clubs.

